Hey there! This is the 1st time I am writing anything, but I have wanted to so many times! I have been watching these at-home yoga videos religiously since August of 2012 (minus some time off during pregnancy lol), and man...I tell everyone I know about Yoga with Adriene.  When I noticed that you were on the news, I flipped. The fact that I can keep getting into your videos regularly, having to make time for it when kids are running around and so many things need attention, that is really something for me.  You had me at, "Get hot for your inner teacher..." amongst many other things- you have been like a ray of light and a breath of fresh air, all wrapped into a super-cool, relatable, person- and not to mention my entire BODY is just insane (well in my opinion for my age and having 4 children...I mean my core is strongggg) Anywhooo, I just have so much admiration and respect for the person you are and how you are able to do this- it is how you are able to really speak to me and how I keep coming back to the mat each day (the hardest part). I am sure you hear this stuff all the time, and honestly I have been wanting to comment on the actual videos for so long, but this was the first time I have used my laptop to get to Yoga with Adriene??? Furthermore, I LOVE BREATH! I already went through it once, but now I am on Day 14 for the 2nd go round.  This is really long, my bad.  Hope you see this one day..... Sincerely, Rosemary B.  =)
As a YWA follower since 2014, who has done all of them already, I really wish there were 2 YWA 30 day journeys per year! These are great.

To anyone looking to start a yoga program and fearing not being fit, this breath series will work for you. I am 62 and had done basically nothing for a year, I used to be fit but was so stiff I didn‚Äôt know if I could last or manage to do this. I have just finished my 6 time through this program, 180 days, and it is a mainstay of my life and fitness and breath. I cannot tell you the difference in my flexibility, movement, breath work, meditation and strength, from the beginning until now. I am so very grateful for the opportunity to experience these 30 days at the beginning of the year with the rest of the community! I have spent the past year exploring all of your videos and have done ALL of the 30 day programs, as I committed myself to a daily yoga practice in 2020. It has helped me to work through a back injury, given me better mobility and strength, helped me to find a deeper sense of self as I have worked on really tough stuff in therapy, and given structure to my day that was desperately needed in this pandemic time. I just published a blog post about my journey this past year, and wanted to share it with you: 
https://wellspringenergyworks.com/daily-yoga-practice-reaping-rewards/ 
Thank you, Adriene, for your beautiful spirit and loving approach. It has made all the difference. Love and Peace.
